# Simulated Data Pipeline
import numpy as np
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import seaborn as sns
import statsmodels.api as sm
from statsmodels.discrete.discrete_model import Logit
from sklearn.decomposition import PCA
from sklearn.manifold import TSNE
from sklearn.cluster import KMeans
from sklearn.ensemble import RandomForestClassifier
from sklearn.metrics import accuracy_score

np.random.seed(42)

# ---- Data Simulation ----
n_individuals = 100
n_snps = 20
allele_freq = 0.3
genotypes = np.random.binomial(2, allele_freq, size=(n_individuals, n_snps))
snp_names = [f'SNP_{i+1}' for i in range(n_snps)]
df_geno = pd.DataFrame(genotypes, columns=snp_names)

# Simulate binary phenotype with SNP_5 affecting outcome
intercept = -1.0  
beta = 1.5  
log_odds = intercept + beta * df_geno['SNP_5']
probabilities = 1 / (1 + np.exp(-log_odds))
phenotype = np.random.binomial(1, probabilities, n_individuals)
df_pheno = pd.DataFrame({'Phenotype': phenotype})

# Merge genotype and phenotype data
df_sim = pd.concat([df_geno, df_pheno], axis=1)
print("Simulated Data (first 5 rows):")
print(df_sim.head())

# ---- EDA ----
print("\nGenotype Summary Statistics (Simulated):")
print(df_geno.describe())
plt.figure(figsize=(6,4))
sns.countplot(x='SNP_5', data=df_geno)
plt.title("Distribution of SNP_5 (Simulated)")
plt.xlabel("Genotype")
plt.ylabel("Count")
plt.show()

plt.figure(figsize=(6,4))
sns.countplot(x='Phenotype', data=df_pheno)
plt.title("Phenotype Distribution (Simulated)")
plt.xlabel("Phenotype")
plt.ylabel("Count")
plt.show()

# ---- Dimensionality Reduction ----
pca = PCA(n_components=2)
pca_result = pca.fit_transform(df_geno)
df_sim['PCA1'] = pca_result[:, 0]
df_sim['PCA2'] = pca_result[:, 1]
plt.figure(figsize=(6,6))
sns.scatterplot(x='PCA1', y='PCA2', hue='Phenotype', data=df_sim, palette='Set1')
plt.title("PCA of Simulated Genotype Data")
plt.show()

tsne = TSNE(n_components=2, random_state=42, perplexity=10)
tsne_result = tsne.fit_transform(df_geno)
df_sim['tSNE1'] = tsne_result[:, 0]
df_sim['tSNE2'] = tsne_result[:, 1]
plt.figure(figsize=(6,6))
sns.scatterplot(x='tSNE1', y='tSNE2', hue='Phenotype', data=df_sim, palette='Set2')
plt.title("t-SNE of Simulated Genotype Data")
plt.show()

# ---- Clustering (Simulated) ----
kmeans_sim = KMeans(n_clusters=2, random_state=42)
clusters_sim = kmeans_sim.fit_predict(pca_result)
df_sim['cluster'] = clusters_sim
plt.figure(figsize=(6,6))
sns.scatterplot(x='PCA1', y='PCA2', hue='cluster', data=df_sim, palette='Set1', style=df_sim['Phenotype'])
plt.title("K-Means Clustering on Simulated PCA")
plt.show()

# ---- Association Testing (Simulated) ----
p_values_sim = []
for snp in snp_names:
    X = df_sim[[snp]]
    X = sm.add_constant(X)
    y = df_sim['Phenotype']
    try:
        model = Logit(y, X)
        result = model.fit(disp=0)
        p = result.pvalues[snp]
    except Exception as e:
        p = np.nan
        print(f"Error in {snp}: {e}")
    p_values_sim.append(p)
df_results_sim = pd.DataFrame({'SNP': snp_names, 'p_value': p_values_sim})
df_results_sim['-log10(p)'] = -np.log10(df_results_sim['p_value'])
print("\nAssociation Results (Simulated):")
print(df_results_sim)

plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
plt.scatter(range(1, n_snps+1), df_results_sim['-log10(p)'], color='blue')
plt.xlabel('SNP Index')
plt.ylabel('-log10(p-value)')
plt.title('Manhattan Plot (Simulated)')
plt.axhline(y=-np.log10(0.05/n_snps), color='red', linestyle='--', label='Bonferroni threshold')
plt.legend()
plt.show()

# ---- Feature Selection & Classification (Simulated) ----
from sklearn.ensemble import RandomForestClassifier
rf_sim = RandomForestClassifier(n_estimators=100, random_state=42)
X_rf_sim = df_geno.values
y_rf_sim = df_sim['Phenotype'].values
rf_sim.fit(X_rf_sim, y_rf_sim)
y_pred_sim = rf_sim.predict(X_rf_sim)
acc_sim = accuracy_score(y_rf_sim, y_pred_sim)
print("\nRandom Forest Accuracy (Simulated): {:.2f}%".format(acc_sim * 100))

importances_sim = rf_sim.feature_importances_
feat_imp_sim = pd.DataFrame({'SNP': snp_names, 'Importance': importances_sim}).sort_values(by='Importance', ascending=False)
print("\nFeature Importances (Simulated):")
print(feat_imp_sim)
plt.figure(figsize=(8,4))
sns.barplot(x='SNP', y='Importance', data=feat_imp_sim, palette='viridis')
plt.title("Random Forest Feature Importances (Simulated)")
plt.xticks(rotation=45)
plt.show()

# 3. Real Dataset Pipeline
# -------------------------------

# ---- Data Loading & Preprocessing (Real) ----
df_real = pd.read_csv("GCST90310248.tsv\EWAS_PUMMA_SBP-update.tsv", sep="\t")
print("Real Data Initial Shape:", df_real.shape)
print(df_real.head())

# Rename columns for consistency
df_real = df_real.rename(columns={
    'chromosome': 'CHR',
    'base_pair_location': 'BP',
    'p_value': 'P',
    'beta': 'BETA'
})
df_real = df_real.dropna(subset=['CHR', 'BP', 'P', 'BETA'])
df_real['CHR'] = df_real['CHR'].astype(str)
df_real['BP'] = df_real['BP'].astype(int)
df_real['P'] = pd.to_numeric(df_real['P'], errors='coerce')
df_real['BETA'] = pd.to_numeric(df_real['BETA'], errors='coerce')
df_real['neg_log_p'] = -np.log10(df_real['P'])
df_real['ind'] = range(len(df_real))

# ---- Manhattan Plot (Real) ----
plt.figure(figsize=(15, 6))
colors = ['#1f77b4', '#ff7f0e']
df_grouped = df_real.groupby('CHR')
x_labels = []
x_labels_pos = []

for i, (name, group) in enumerate(df_grouped):
    group.plot(kind='scatter', x='ind', y='neg_log_p', color=colors[i % len(colors)],
               ax=plt.gca(), s=10, label=f"Chr {name}")
    x_labels.append(name)
    x_labels_pos.append((group['ind'].iloc[-1] + group['ind'].iloc[0]) // 2)

plt.axhline(y=-np.log10(5e-8), color='red', linestyle='--', label='Genome-wide significance')
plt.xticks(x_labels_pos, x_labels, rotation=90)
plt.xlabel('Chromosome')
plt.ylabel('-log10(p-value)')
plt.title('Manhattan Plot for Systolic Blood Pressure')
plt.legend()
plt.tight_layout()
plt.show()

# ---- Top Significant Variants (Real) ----
significant_real = df_real[df_real['P'] < 5e-8]
top_snps_real = significant_real.sort_values('P').head(10)
print("\nTop 10 Significant Variants (Real):")
print(top_snps_real[['CHR', 'BP', 'P', 'BETA']])

# ---- Clustering (Real) ----
X_real = df_real[['BP', 'BETA']].dropna()
kmeans_real = KMeans(n_clusters=3, random_state=0)
df_real.loc[X_real.index, 'cluster'] = kmeans_real.fit_predict(X_real)
plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
sns.scatterplot(data=df_real, x='BP', y='BETA', hue='cluster', palette='Set1', alpha=0.7)
plt.title('Clustering of SNPs by Position and Effect Size (Real Data)')
plt.xlabel('Base Pair Position')
plt.ylabel('Effect Size (Beta)')
plt.legend(title='Cluster')
plt.tight_layout()
plt.show()
